					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Just make sure that kind of behavior doesn't make the enemy <em>too</em> unpredictable, especially in situations where you need to dodge/attack it.<br /><br />Like, imagine if it's coming right for you at a specific speed, and you prepare to jump over it, but just as it's getting close it randomly changes to a much slower speed, and you land on it on the way down.<br />That's the kind of stuff we usually call &quot;hard for the wrong reasons&quot;.</div>

